025/**
026 * DTO for an HTML <a class="doclink" href="https://www.w3.org/TR/html5/embedded-content-0.html#the-video-element">&lt;video&gt;</a>
027 * element.
028 *
029 * <p>
030 * The video element is used to embed video content in an HTML document. It provides a way to include
031 * video files that can be played by the browser's built-in video player. The video element supports
032 * multiple video formats and provides various attributes for controlling playback, appearance, and
033 * behavior. It can contain source elements to specify multiple video formats for browser compatibility.
034 *
035 * <h5 class='section'>Examples:</h5>
036 * <p class='bcode w800'>
037 *    <jk>import static</jk> org.apache.juneau.bean.html5.HtmlBuilder.*;
038 * 
039 *    <jc>// Simple video with controls</jc>
040 *    Video <jv>simple</jv> = <jsm>video</jsm>()
041 *       .src(<js>"movie.mp4"</js>)
042 *       .controls(<jk>true</jk>)
043 *       .width(640)
044 *       .height(360);
045 * 
046 *    <jc>// Video with multiple sources</jc>
047 *    Video <jv>multiple</jv> = <jsm>video</jsm>(
048 *       <jsm>source</jsm>().src(<js>"movie.mp4"</js>).type(<js>"video/mp4"</js>),
049 *       <jsm>source</jsm>().src(<js>"movie.webm"</js>).type(<js>"video/webm"</js>),
050 *       <jsm>source</jsm>().src(<js>"movie.ogg"</js>).type(<js>"video/ogg"</js>)
051 *    ).controls(<jk>true</jk>);
052 * 
053 *    <jc>// Autoplay video (muted for browser compatibility)</jc>
054 *    Video <jv>autoplay</jv> = <jsm>video</jsm>()
055 *       .src(<js>"intro.mp4"</js>)
056 *       .autoplay(<jk>true</jk>)
057 *       .muted(<jk>true</jk>)
058 *       .loop(<jk>true</jk>);
059 * 
060 *    <jc>// Video with poster image</jc>
061 *    Video <jv>poster</jv> = <jsm>video</jsm>()
062 *       .src(<js>"trailer.mp4"</js>)
063 *       .poster(<js>"trailer-poster.jpg"</js>)
064 *       .controls(<jk>true</jk>)
065 *       .width(800)
066 *       .height(450);
067 * 
068 *    <jc>// Video with custom styling</jc>
069 *    Video <jv>styled</jv> = <jsm>video</jsm>()
070 *       .src("presentation.mp4")
071 *       .controls(true)
072 *       ._class("video-player")
073 *       .style("border: 2px solid #ccc; border-radius: 8px;");
074 * 
075 *    // Video with event handlers
076 *    Video interactive = new Video()
077 *       .src("tutorial.mp4")
078 *       .controls(true)
079 *       .onplay("trackVideoPlay()")
080 *       .onended("showNextVideo()");
081 * </p>
082 *
083 * <p>
084 * The following convenience methods are provided for constructing instances of this bean:
085 * <ul class='javatree'>
086 *    <li class='jc'>{@link HtmlBuilder}
087 *    <ul class='javatree'>
088 *       <li class='jm'>{@link HtmlBuilder#video() video()}
089 *       <li class='jm'>{@link HtmlBuilder#video(Object, Object...) video(Object, Object...)}
090 *    </ul>
091 * </ul>
092 * </p>
093 *
094 * <h5 class='section'>See Also:</h5><ul>
095 *    <li class='link'><a class="doclink" href="https://juneau.apache.org/docs/topics/JuneauBeanHtml5">juneau-bean-html5</a>
096 * </ul>
097 */
098@Bean(typeName="video")
099@FluentSetters
100public class Video extends HtmlElementContainer {
101
102   /**
103    * Creates an empty {@link Video} element.
104    */
105   public Video() {}
106
107   /**
108    * Creates a {@link Video} element with the specified {@link Video#src(Object)} attribute.
109    *
110    * @param src The {@link Video#src(Object)} attribute.
111    */
112   public Video(Object src) {
113      src(src);
114   }
115
116   /**
117    * <a class="doclink" href="https://www.w3.org/TR/html5/embedded-content-0.html#attr-media-autoplay">autoplay</a>
118    * attribute.
119    *
120    * <p>
121    * Hint that the media resource can be started automatically when the page is loaded.
122    *
123    * <p>
124    * This attribute uses deminimized values:
125    * <ul>
126    *    <li><jk>false</jk> - Attribute is not added</li>
127    *    <li><jk>true</jk> - Attribute is added as <js>"autoplay"</js></li>
128    *    <li>Other values - Passed through as-is</li>
129    * </ul>
130    *
131    * @param autoplay
132    *    The new value for this attribute.
133    *    Typically a {@link Boolean} or {@link String}.
134    * @return This object.
135    */
136   public Video autoplay(Object value) {
137      attr("autoplay", deminimize(value, "autoplay"));
138      return this;
139   }
140
141   /**
142    * <a class="doclink" href="https://www.w3.org/TR/html5/embedded-content-0.html#attr-media-controls">controls</a>
143    * attribute.
144    *
145    * <p>
146    * Show user agent controls.
147    *
148    * <p>
149    * This attribute uses deminimized values:
150    * <ul>
151    *    <li><jk>false</jk> - Attribute is not added</li>
152    *    <li><jk>true</jk> - Attribute is added as <js>"controls"</js></li>
153    *    <li>Other values - Passed through as-is</li>
154    * </ul>
155    *
156    * @param controls
157    *    The new value for this attribute.
158    *    Typically a {@link Boolean} or {@link String}.
159    * @return This object.
160    */
161   public Video controls(Object value) {
162      attr("controls", deminimize(value, "controls"));
163      return this;
164   }
165
166   /**
167    * <a class="doclink" href="https://www.w3.org/TR/html5/embedded-content-0.html#attr-media-crossorigin">crossorigin</a>
168    * attribute.
169    *
170    * <p>
171    * Specifies how the element handles cross-origin requests for CORS (Cross-Origin Resource Sharing).
172    *
173    * <p>
174    * Possible values:
175    * <ul>
176    *    <li><js>"anonymous"</js> - Cross-origin requests are made without credentials</li>
177    *    <li><js>"use-credentials"</js> - Cross-origin requests include credentials</li>
178    * </ul>
179    *
180    * @param crossorigin How to handle cross-origin requests.
181    * @return This object.
182    */
183   public Video crossorigin(String value) {
184      attr("crossorigin", value);
185      return this;
186   }

208    * <p>
209    * Causes the media to automatically restart from the beginning when it reaches the end.

219   /**
220    * <a class="doclink" href="https://www.w3.org/TR/html5/embedded-content-0.html#attr-media-mediagroup">mediagroup</a>
221    * attribute.
222    *
223    * <p>
224    * Groups multiple media elements together so they can be controlled as a single unit. All media elements
225    * with the same mediagroup value will share the same MediaController, allowing synchronized playback.
226    *
227    * <p>
228    * This is useful for creating synchronized audio/video presentations or multiple camera angles.
229    *
230    * @param mediagroup The name of the media group to join.
231    * @return This object.
232    */
233   public Video mediagroup(String value) {
234      attr("mediagroup", value);
235      return this;
236   }
237
238   /**
239    * <a class="doclink" href="https://www.w3.org/TR/html5/embedded-content-0.html#attr-media-muted">muted</a>
240    * attribute.
241    *
242    * <p>
243    * Mutes the audio output by default. Useful for autoplay videos where audio should be disabled initially.
244    *
245    * @param muted If <jk>true</jk>, the media will be muted by default.
246    * @return This object.
247    */
248   public Video muted(Object value) {
249      attr("muted", value);
250      return this;
251   }
252
253   /**
254    * <a class="doclink" href="https://www.w3.org/TR/html5/embedded-content-0.html#attr-video-poster">poster</a>
255    * attribute.
256    *
257    * <p>
258    * Specifies an image to display as a placeholder before the video starts playing. This image is shown
259    * while the video is loading or before the user clicks play.
260    *
261    * <p>
262    * The poster image should be representative of the video content and help users understand what the video contains.
263    *
264    * @param poster The URL of the poster image to display before video playback.
265    * @return This object.
266    */
267   public Video poster(String value) {
268      attr("poster", value);
269      return this;
270   }
271
272   /**
273    * <a class="doclink" href="https://www.w3.org/TR/html5/embedded-content-0.html#attr-media-preload">preload</a>
274    * attribute.
275    *
276    * <p>
277    * Specifies how the browser should load the media resource.
278    *
279    * <p>
280    * Possible values:
281    * <ul>
282    *    <li><js>"none"</js> - Do not preload the media</li>
283    *    <li><js>"metadata"</js> - Preload only metadata (duration, dimensions, etc.)</li>
284    *    <li><js>"auto"</js> - Preload the entire media file (default)</li>
285    * </ul>
286    *
287    * @param preload How much of the media to preload.
288    * @return This object.
289    */
290   public Video preload(String value) {
291      attr("preload", value);
292      return this;
293   }
294
295   /**
296    * <a class="doclink" href="https://www.w3.org/TR/html5/embedded-content-0.html#attr-media-src">src</a> attribute.
297    *
298    * <p>
299    * Address of the resource.
300    *
301    * <p>
302    * The value can be of any of the following types: {@link URI}, {@link URL}, {@link String}.
303    * Strings must be valid URIs.
304    *
305    * <p>
306    * URIs defined by {@link UriResolver} can be used for values.
307    *
308    * @param src
309    *    The new value for this attribute.
310    *    Typically a {@link URL} or {@link String}.
311    * @return This object.
312    */
313   public Video src(Object value) {
314      attrUri("src", value);
315      return this;
316   }
317
318   /**
319    * <a class="doclink" href="https://www.w3.org/TR/html5/embedded-content-0.html#attr-dim-width">width</a> attribute.
320    *
321    * <p>
322    * Horizontal dimension.
323    *
324    * @param width
325    *    The new value for this attribute.
326    *    Typically a {@link Number} or {@link String}.
327    * @return This object.
328    */
329   public Video width(Object value) {
330      attr("width", value);
331      return this;
332   }
